Run Assignment Rules for Einstein Case Classification

You need the Service Cloud Einstein add-on license to use Einstein Case Routing.

Einstein Case Classification automatically saves predicted field values to a case, and Einstein Case Routing can use your existing case routing logic to route the case to the right agent.

To build and manage Einstein Case Classification:

View Setup
Customize Application
Manage Profiles and Permission Sets
Edit on cases or Modify All Data

In Setup, enter Einstein Classification in the Quick Find box, select Einstein Classification. Choose whether to run case assignment rules, skills-based routing, or both. If no rules are defined, cases aren't routed.

Automate Value for a field in your model updates the case field when the prediction meets the confidence threshold. When a case is updated, Einstein Case Routing runs the selected routing rules.

If using custom logic for queue-based or skills-based routing, subscribe to AIUpdateRecordEvent and rerun your routing logic after notification.
title: Running Assignment Rules for Einstein Case Classification
